Do not use one fully shared vendor account. It creates check-then-act and read-modify-write risks: people can overwrite carts, addresses, shipping choices, and PO/reference fields, or place duplicate urgent orders. The low-friction fix is one vendor org account with individual logins, shared payment methods, role limits, default shipping/address locks, and mandatory order notes tied to the requester or incident. If the vendor cannot support that, use a shared password vault checkout plus a simple rule: one person checks out the credential for one order at a time and records the order ID immediately.
